McGraw Conglomerate Corporation intends to acquire mature, profitable business operations for the benefit of our share holders..
We are offering up to $15 million in common stock to fund the investment and acquisition of business operations 










OFFERING CIRCULAR
Invest Now


SHARE

         
Link Copied




















COMPANY OVERVIEW
ADVISORY BOARD
INVESTMENT OFFERING
INDUSTRIES



 McGraw Conglomerate Corporation acquires, and invests into mature, revenue generating business operations, with the intention to control revenue streams and acquire business operations in profitable industries. McGraw will adhere to a growth by acquisition model inside business sectors that have traditionally, and recently, proven to be safe harbors for capital investment. We are offering up to $15 million in common stock to fund the investment and acquisition of business operations inside the industries of Oil and Clean Energy, Automotive Dealerships, Dealership Services, Financial Services, Insurance Services, Construction, and Entertainment Fitness. The offering is being conducted pursuant to Regulation A. 
OUR INDUSTRIES
Entertainment & Fitness
McGraw intends to acquire a position in the wildly popular sport of Mixed Martial Arts (MMA), with the acquisition of an athletic training facility and also an MMA events promotion company.
Financial & Insurance
McGraw intends to acquire a Financial and Insurance Company to offer loan products and insurance services.
Automotive & Dealership
McGraw intends to acquire a thriving car dealership and a mature dealership services company.
Construction & Real Estate
McGraw intends to acquire a construction company to construct luxury residential homes as well as income producing medical facilities.
Oil & Clean Energy
McGraw Conglomerate intends to help the United States achieve energy independence with the acquisition and development of existing oil fields and the development of U.S. renewable energy platforms.



SUBSCRIPTION

 Total Investment 
$15,000,000

 Maximum Investment 
2,500,000 Shares  $15,000,000

 Minimum Investment 
200 Shares  $1200.00

 Price/Common 
$6.00

OFFERING DOCUMENTS

OFFERING CIRCULAR VIEW
 



Invest Now





Ken McGraw
McGraw Conglomerate Corporation CEO
For his 25-year career, Ken McGraw has seen success in the conceiving and development of both small and large business operations. Ken has founded many companies and has seen great success in a wide variety of industries.
As the Founder and CEO of multiple companies, Ken has decades of experience managing large groups of individuals, small business owners and corporations. Ken has helped many companies in varied industries, grow from start up to profitability. This has prepared Ken to become the CEO of McGraw Conglomerate Corporation.
Ken brings decades of experience in sales and marketing and a deep knowledge of complex business operations to McGraw Conglomerate. This experience is relevant and necessary as the CEO of a conglomerate/holding company, working in multiple industries across multiple platforms.
In 1991, Ken developed McGraw Marketing, a nationwide sales and marketing company, to organize hundreds of independent business owners to construct a nationwide sales organization that created a significant revenue stream for his company as well as many smaller companies under his tutelage.
In 1996, Ken founded TCM Incorporated, a nationwide corporate consulting firm. As the CEO, Ken would consult for many different businesses in a wide variety of industries. Ken is in demand as a sales and marketing expert, helping underperforming companies with generating sales and retooling business operations to transform into large and diverse corporate entities.
In 1998, Ken founded 4M Financial Corp, a residential and commercial mortgage brokerage operation. As the CEO, Ken would lead a team of professionals to success in the world of finance, as a residential and commercial finance operation.
In 2006, McGraw founded Excellent Funding, Inc., a multi-state wholesale banking operation. As the COO, Ken ensured Excellent Funding was a successful multi-state wholesale banking operation that grew from the mid-west, reaching to the southern United States, and servicing hundreds of full service mortgage operations.
As the CEO of McGraw Conglomerate Corporation, Ken will utilize his extensive experience as a Top Executive, to ensure McGraw Conglomerate grows at a steady pace and provides an increasing return on investment to its shareholders.


 



Chris Shefts
C&C Kolorpatch Inc President and CEO
For the past 18 years Chris has worked in the Automotive Industry. Chris has founded and operated multiple automotive operations over the course of his career.
As a franchise owner in the automotive industry, Chris developed multiple territories in the Midwest and led his company in record sales and profitability. Chris is an industry expert in recruiting and developing talented salesmen and industry technicians that helped him set performance records in the automotive industry.
As CEO of a dealership services company, Chris has maintained the #1 ranking in profitability over his competitors for the last 18 years. Chris is well skilled in current automotive sales and operations standards and techniques.
As an industry performance leader and experienced operations manager, Chris is a welcome addition to the McGraw Conglomerate Corporation Advisory Board.


 



Daniel Lawton
Mortgage and Financial Services Professional
Daniel Lawton brings a depth of knowledge and hands on experience to the McGraw Conglomerate as a Financial Services Advisor. After graduating with honors from Eastern Illinois University, Daniel quickly put his talent to work as a manager for a nationwide health and fitness corporation. Daniel managed a large staff of employees where he was awarded the title of “Key Performance Indicator Regional Lead”.
Daniel is in demand as a skilled salesmen and operations professional in the financial services industry. He has extensive experience in training career professionals in industry concepts and procedures. He is also well versed in training industry salesmen inside a finance environment, for the achievement of corporate goals.
As a member of the management team for a regional banking operation, Daniel also has extensive experience in a retail banking environment. Daniel has used his financial management experience to organize sales teams and work with operations team members to achieve great success inside the competitive world of mortgage and finance.


 



Danny Stojanovic
ADR Construction, President and CEO
Since 2003, Danny Stojanovic has been the Chief Executive of a midwestern real estate development company. Danny is highly skilled in both residential and commercial construction. Danny comes to the McGraw Conglomerate as an advisor with 14 years’ experience as a builder, developer, and general contractor.
His work includes high end, luxury single family, multi-unit residential, muliti-unit commercial, and large scale retail commercial properties.
Danny’s will advise the construction and real estate division for McGraw Conglomerate, and lend his expertise to all company construction project identification, development, and completion.
Danny’s industry experience and history of developing exceptional real estate projects, is a valuable addition to the McGraw Conglomerate Corporation Advisory Board.


 



Lori McGraw
FitGirl Fitness, Founder Health and Fitness Manager Fitness Instruction and Competition Professional
Lori McGraw has enjoyed a 29-year career in the Health and Fitness Industry. Lori is an ASFA Certified Advanced Personal Trainer and has held certifications in PIYO, Turbo Kick, TRX, and Insanity. Lori’s specialties include circuit training, weight management, weight training, personal training and fitness boot camps.
For decades, Lori has worked in the fitness industry as a fitness management professional. Lori has managed locations for both small and large fitness corporations. Her expert management helped her consistently achieve the top awards for production and income at her locations. Her experience and understanding of fitness sales and operations make her advice highly sought after in the fitness industry.
Lori’s ability to help individuals reach personal fitness goals and her expertise in health and fitness management make her a welcome addition to the McGraw Conglomerate Corporation Advisory Board.




Acquisition of Existing Operations and Revenue Streams:
All target acquisitions, and investments under consideration by McGraw, will be well established in their respective industry, possess a robust revenue stream, and prove capable of long term growth after new investment. McGraw will not acquire, nor invest in, any start up or speculative business operation or entity. 
Diversified Industries and Low Beta Investments:
McGraw intends to invest in businesses across a wide variety of industries, offering the safety net of a diversified portfolio. McGraw will be a safe harbor and hedge against any single market fluctuation, by acquiring equity positions in well-established and profitable businesses in wide ranging business sectors. The company is committed to invest in “low beta” or “low risk” business operations that show very low volatility, and present a steady return over the long term to the average investor. 
Early to Mid-Staged Business Life Cycle Opportunities, Presenting Long View Returns:
McGraw intends to acquire entities who are viewed as in the early or mid-stages of their business life cycle, that present McGraw with an increasing return over the long term. McGraw will not invest in entities who show little or no potential for growth in their main or affiliated lines of business. 
Ethical Standards of Operation:
To be considered for acquisition or investment by McGraw, entities must have proven to operate with the highest ethical standards and be well respected in their industry and with their customer base. 
Key Employee and Management Retention:
McGraw will pursue investments that ensure low turnover among employees and management inside the target business operation. McGraw will aim to retain all current employees, management, and ownership of the target business, to facilitate a smooth transition of ownership with no interruption of sales and operations activities. 
Re-investment Supporting Healthy Company Growth:
McGraw intends to re-invest from profits into The Company and target acquisitions, in support of company personnel and operations. McGraw will maintain balance, seeking the equivalent investment of attention and resources inside the company itself, and among its subsidiaries. We will maintain a positive work environment and seek to grow our respective investments in all aspects of business activities.




Entertainment & Fitness
Entertainment and Fitness Industries have gone hand in hand since the inception of the World Wrestling Entertainment (“WWE”) in 1979. WWE is an American publicly traded company that deals primarily in professional wrestling with major revenue sources also coming from film, music, product licensing and direct product sales.
The Ultimate Fighting Championship (“UFC”) is the largest mixed martial arts (“MMA”) promoter in the world and features most of the top-ranked fighters in the sport. UFC recently sold for $4 billion, the most expensive transaction for an organization in sports history. While we may not be as successful, we hope to emulate such models like the WWE and the UFC, McGraw plans to capitalize on this now largely mainstream MMA industry, as a licensed promotion company, and athlete training and recruiting division for the MMA industry. Specifically, McGraw intends to acquire a licensed and proven training center for MMA athletes that supplies professional talent directly to the MMA industry.
McGraw also intends to acquire an MMA events promotion company that would be licensed by one of the existing MMA entities and would be responsible for regional MMA events that would be televised nationwide to a large and growing audience. By entering this space, McGraw believes it will have acquired a highly lucrative component of a wildly successful and profitable industry. Entertainment Fitness has very few corporate players, and McGraw will seek to establish itself as a serious player, incurring only a modest dollar commitment.


 



Financial Services & Insurance Services
Ken McGraw, the Principal of McGraw, has significant experience in the Financial and Banking industries. Mr. McGraw intends (with necessary funding) to acquire a company that offers loans for residential and commercial real estate, small business loans, car loans, as well as Insurance and Re-Insurance Services.
McGraw also intends to acquire, again with adequate funding) a Finance Company as well as an insurance and/or re-insurance operation, Mr. McGraw having extensive prior experience in these Financial Industries. Consequently, we believe the Company will be able to invest wisely in low beta, highly successful operations, showing potential for significant revenue with minimal investment.
McGraw, in addition, intends to seek ways to utilize its holdings in the Finance and Banking sector to reduce the cost of borrowing for all its other acquisitions and holdings.


 



Automotive Services & Dealership Services
Additional business sectors that have traditionally, and recently, proven (in our view) to be a safe harbor for capital investment, are the Automotive Dealership and Dealership Services Industry.
The Company, with adequate funding, expects to acquire an Automotive Dealership Services Company (or companies) to offer on-site dealership services, regionally…if not nationwide. Dealership Services is a niche industry that services auto, boat, and airplane dealerships.
We intend to acquire such dealership services to enrich the automotive holdings for the Company, offering the ability to market goods and services across multiple industry platforms.
McGraw intends to acquire a thriving Automotive Dealership once the adequate funding has been achieved. Pairing Dealership Services with an Automotive Dealership owned by McGraw, will create (in our opinion) a symbiotic revenue relationship that should benefit The Company.


 



Construction & Real Estate
Our analysis suggests that the Construction and Real Estate sectors are showing signs of growth and such market sectors have traditionally been safe harbor investments for long-term investors. Along with traditional construction plans for high-end residential and income-producing commercial buildings.
If successful in its money raise, McGraw plans to operate inside a niche market of the construction industry: medical facilities construction and management. The medical field (especially senior care or “long-term care”), we are convinced, is soon to experience its largest growth cycle in a generation.
We believe the rate of retirees is set to exceed all generations by a large multiple. Very specifically, McGraw plans to combine the stable and increasing construction industry with the stable and high growth long-term care industry.
McGraw intends to join with a well-established and experienced medical group, servicing a significant patient list. The Company (with adequate funding) will be able to build up multiple medical facilities, and grand open each location 100% pre-sold and occupied.
We expect to be able to staff and manage those facilities with properly licensed medical staff and operated by the contemplated partner/joint venture medical group.
Upon completion of each facility, McGraw intends to maintain options to retain ownership of each property and participate in revenue sharing, acting as the landlord, or negotiate a price to sell each property to the occupying medical group at a profit.


 



Oil & Clean Energy
McGraw intends to invest in actively producing oil wells in the southern United States and explore future investments in clean energy production. To be considered, oil fields by McGraw, must be producing hundreds of barrels of American oil every day, and delivering it to refineries at a brisk pace. Such acquisition would, we believe, be consistent with the Company’s objective to invest only in successful, low beta, revenue producing businesses.
In fact, we believe we can acquire operating companies with existing infrastructure, already in place in each location, thereby, in our view, providing McGraw zero startup costs and ensuring all investment dollars from the Company are ‘above ground’ and can contribute to growing an existing revenue stream into a major profit center.
McGraw will also seek acquisitions that contribute to U.S. energy independence in other ways, such as harnessing wind energy. McGraw intends to work with government agencies, and clean energy experts, to decide upon the appropriate course of action for the Company to enter the clean energy industry.
McGraw’s objective, among others, is to help the United States achieve energy independence in an environmentally responsible manner.


 









